{"text": "(6.14)\n\nBelow we will prove that the generator of rotations around the axis n is:\n\nLn = \u20d7n \u00b7 (r \u00d7 p)\n\n(6.15)\n\nwhere:\n\n\u02c6r = (\u02c6x, \u02c6y, \u02c6z)\n\n(6.16)\n\n\u02c6p = (\u02c6px, \u02c6py, \u02c6pz)\n\nProof: We shall show that both sides of the equation give the same result if they operate on any basis state r\u27e9. This\n\nmeans that we have an operator identity.\n\nR(\u03b4\u20d7\u03a6) r\u27e9= RE( \u20d7\u03b4\u03a6)r\u27e9= r + \u03b4\u20d7\u03a6 \u00d7 r\u27e9= D(\u03b4\u20d7\u03a6 \u00d7 r) r\u27e9\n\n(6.17)\n\n= [\u02c61 \u2212i(\u03b4\u20d7\u03a6 \u00d7 r) \u00b7 \u02c6p] r\u27e9= [\u02c61 \u2212i\u02c6p \u00b7 \u03b4\u20d7\u03a6 \u00d7 r] r\u27e9= [\u02c61 \u2212i\u02c6p \u00b7 \u03b4\u20d7\u03a6 \u00d7 \u02c6r] r\u27e9\n\n29\n\nSo we get the following operator identity:\n\nR(\u03b4\u20d7\u03a6) = \u02c61 \u2212i\u02c6p \u00b7 \u03b4\u20d7\u03a6 \u00d7 \u02c6r\n\n(6.18)\n\nWhich can also be written (by exploiting the cyclic property of the triple vectorial multiplication):\n\nR(\u03b4\u20d7\u03a6) = \u02c61 \u2212i\u03b4\u20d7\u03a6 \u00b7 (\u02c6r \u00d7 \u02c6p)\n\n(6.19)\n\nFrom here we get the desired result. Note: The more common procedure to derive this identity is based on expanding\n\nthe rotated wavefunction \u03c8(RE(\u2212\u03b4\u03a6)r) = \u03c8(r \u2212\u03b4\u03a6 \u00d7 r), and exploiting the association p 7\u2192\u2212i\u2207.\n\n====== [6.4] Algebraic characterization of rotations\n\nA unitary operator \u02c6D realizes a translation a in the basis which is determined by an observable \u02c6x if we have the\n\nequality \u02c6D\u22121\u02c6x \u02c6D = \u02c6x + a. Let us prove the analogous statement for rotations: A unitary operator \u02c6R realizes rotation\n\n\u03a6 in the basis which is determined by an observable \u02c6r if we have the equality\n\n\u02c6R\u22121\u02c6ri \u02c6R\n\n=\n\nX\n\nj\n\nRE\n\nij \u02c6rj\n\n(6.20)\n\nwhere RE is the Euclidean rotation matrix. This relation constitutes an algebraic characterization of the rotation\n\noperator.", "embedding": [0.008732693, -0.040441927, 0.027146708, -0.050633196, 0.028212914, -0.031828027, -0.023290131, -0.01988099, -0.061092723, 0.08410132, 0.060564075, 0.017574226, -0.004845429, -0.027600722, -0.026733726, -0.0036427605, 0.0040136226, -0.016665282, -0.057403747, 0.02383767, 0.034376223, -0.0037185135, -0.08017508, -0.041524414, -0.010476911, 0.014332585, 0.006942061, 0.013994224, 0.03615289, 0.060006376, 0.02776913, -0.040080015, 0.035847135, -0.01838865, 0.00861925, -0.0017918544, -0.00070231134, -0.004641706, 0.046393294, -0.04531177, 0.030354602, 0.006915544, 0.0065580253, -0.025577927, -0.04579907, -0.019265044, -0.024963202, 0.013619708, -0.032498356, -0.060197078, 0.01601344, 0.007421053, 0.023620797, -0.045115326, -0.029980414, 0.00092999457, 0.03014336, -0.016391873, -0.018507708, 0.046383735, 0.021765012, -0.018848857, -0.010625984, -0.074540354, -0.009378607, 0.012173942, -0.01850154, 0.030457605, 0.009355247, -0.07845727, 0.005892148, -0.026504932, -0.030704886, -0.008497535, -0.030974783, 0.056567054, -0.008846641, -0.02059625, -0.06765356, 0.025517331, -0.010000715, -0.02392302, -0.029147249, 0.012258555, 0.00045921883, -0.012476065, 0.016132059, -0.024171947, 0.007993607, -0.041110218, 0.02519794, 0.046934836, -0.022837395, 0.0074146194, 0.042006392, 0.027042426, -0.0021979609, 0.04452516, 0.05455109, -0.005416072, 0.010355899, 0.054245055, -0.011027713, 0.06316081, -0.01513495, 0.027067345, 0.01925331, 0.026351735, -0.0011472267, -0.04094484, 0.062445845, -0.01708558, 0.019431604, 0.02335145, 0.019365152, 0.019832794, 0.018472588, 0.0010590417, -0.02705257, -0.025545923, 0.016342888, 0.0033884142, 0.049120016, 0.04441433, 0.004481315, 0.019947708, -0.006791859, 0.018006437, -0.04898539, -0.0037209734, 0.033788886, -0.012206211, -0.015365741, -0.021666028, -0.025275772, 0.038709268, -0.03208623, 0.018849477, 0.008069909, -0.011003733, 0.030788133, -0.045951672, 0.011019344, 0.0